item.title: Russia's Ruling Party Leading in Elections as Putin Looks to Tighten Grip
item.description: Preliminary results showed United Russia was on course to cement President Vladimir Putin’s control over his country’s main levers of power.

item.title: U.S. Spat With France Shows Challenge of Keeping Allies Unified
item.description: Diplomatic dust-up over security pact among the U.S., Australia and the U.K. comes as Biden administration struggles to maintain unity among its closest friends.

item.title: In Overwhelmed Del Rio, Texas, Migrants Cross the Border Freely
item.description: An estimated 14,000 migrants, many from Haiti, are traveling back and forth to Mexico for supplies as they wait in a makeshift camp.

item.title:

item.description: President Biden is scheduled to address the General Assembly in person as a U.S. nuclear submarine deal with Australia has angered France.

item.title: After Escape From Kabul, an Afghan Family Starts a Long Climb in America
item.description: A family of eight fled Afghanistan and landed in Rochester, N.Y., where they take on the challenges of a new language, culture and economy.

item.title: Israel Captures Last Two Palestinian Militants Who Escaped Prison
item.description: For nearly two weeks, the hunt for the fugitives transfixed the nations, embarrassing Prime Minister Naftali Bennett and emboldening Palestinian attackers.

item.title: Vaccinations Boost the Global Economy, but May Not Cure It Alone
item.description: The Delta variant’s spread shows how Covid-19 can continue to slow economic growth even as governments push to get more people vaccinated.
